Eminent Nigerians including former President Olusegun Obasanjo and the Vice Chancellor, University of Lagos, Prof. Oluwatoyin Ogundipe are to attend the 2nd International Christian Leadership Colloquium being organised in honour of Pastor Ituah Ighodalo for his 61st birthday on March 31, 2022 in Lagos. The convener, Jeremiah Akinsele, said the event themed “The African Christian Leadership: Radical Transformation In Unsettled Times” would hold at Trinity House, Ligali Ayorinde Street, Victoria Island at 11 am. Pastor Paul Adefarasin and Pastor Joseph Obayemi are among the clerics to discuss the theme. 